items.text: Besides their specialty ramen, the green tea cola is very nice too for drinks !
says on sign at door & on website that they close at 10.30pm but staff says today "closing early" at 9.45pm. sub-standards.
Super long queue cos the place is small. But worth the wait! Only one chef but service is quick! Free flow bean sprouts and hard boiled eggs!
Excellent value - try the black spicy ramen
Great tonkotsu broth. One of the best in Singapore!
Must try: flavored egg! 
Super salty, I asked for soft ramen and it wasn't as soft as I expected, not spicy at all even I put lot of chilly powder.. Tried Once enough.
The best ramen in Singapore! Hands down! Very authentic taste with a well made broth. I usually order the ramen with special toppings but be careful, you need to be seriously hungry. Grind sesame!
For those who don't know, the mayo provided on table is to go with the hard boiled eggs. Jap-style of enjoying eggs with ramen!
U can have a plenty of hard boiled eggs for free!!!
Must try the black spicy ramen!
Every 8th August ramen is $5 a bowl.
Вкусные супы. Хорошее обслуживание. Уютно.
Queue starts about an hour before opening time, be sure to queue early!
Free eggs and bean sprouts.....cash only....no credit card or nets.....must try is black spicy ramen
Recommended: Tonkotsu Ramen, Black Spicy Tonkotsu Ramen
Love the red spicy ramen and the free flow of eggs. Usual visit to this ramen place once in every 2 months.
3 outlets in Tanjong Pagar! Shorter waiting time for diners. 2 r @ Orchid Hotel, both along the same stretch. 1 more @ #03-15 100AM
Nice ramen but need to queue. Come at odd times
There is always a queue here. I like their spicy pepperish soup base.
Fragrant & savoury broth with generous servings of ingredients & noodles. And the best thing? free flow of eggs and bean sprouts!
The black tonkutsu ramen is really nicer than I expected and they have quite some side dishes to add.
Best ramen in Singapore. Amazing tonkotsu stock.
First customers for dinner!
Order extra noodles if you still feel hungry! :-)
Original Tonkotsu is really good, but very salty.
Strong recommend for this place. Authentic and affordable, free flow bean sprout and 80% done eggs. Don't go for thick soup, it's really really thick. Go for hard noodles.
Definitely one of the best ramen here. Love the free flow bean sprouts and eggs. Only minus is the queue as the place is really small...
Love their broth
Payment: Cash only. They dun accept NETS or credit card. U wd xpect a joint like dis which serves pricier food  2 hv such convnience but they dun :-(
Get the spicy tonkotsu! Trust me!
Broth amazing
Original Tonkotsu Ramen. You can choose the texture of noodle, richness of soup and less or no oil. Everything to your liking.
Go for original. Black spicy and red spicy just don't cut it.
Black spicy with all toppings is the winning pick!
Tonkotsu noodle with flavored egg is damn tasty!!!
Order outside. Unlimited hard boiled eggs, but it's really the flavoured egg you are here for. Get all the toppings, otherwise all you have is a piece of chashu
Black spice tonkutsu ramen honto ni OIshii da you! Try one with special！イタイダキマス！
Ramen given might not be enough for some. Either add more or fill yourself with the free flow of eggs and bean sprouts! Food is still good though. (;
Going alone can help you jump queue as they will seat you first if they have a single open seat and everyone else has two or three ppl with them
Humongus Seaweed! Love the egg!
Tried their black spicy ramen which isn't spicy, just a hint. I love the free beans sprouts most! It's not plain boiled ones, they marinate theirs in sesame and some Chilli oil. Sedap!
ramen texture hard !
Arguably one of the best ramen stalls in Singapore with its signature tonkotsu (pork bone) broth. The long queues for a table say it all.
DAT BROTH.
Hearty, fatty, savory ramen. Huge line after 5:30 pm. Save a few % with their online coupon (instructions on their main door)
love the boiled egg and seasoned beansprouts side dishes!
Ramen: Design ur own ramen w soup base: plain, red spicy (chilli oil) or black spicy (black pepper). Interesting DIY concept but too salty. Wouldn't q up again for 20mins just 4 dis
The servings are amazing! Free flow sides too!
Delicious broth, free flow of hard boiled eggs & pickled bean sprouts. A must-try ramen place!
Tonkotsu King Ramen is the best option :-) you can have it customized ur own way
I guess this ramen style isn't my thing. The locals like it tho since it was packed. The soup's pork flavour's so thick you'll feel like a baby swine's still in your mouth 30mins later. 6/10
Free flow beansprouts and hard-boiled eggs. Their ramen is pretty good.
The soup base is really fab. If you like spicy options, choose the black over the red ramen. It is fragrant like moderate charred fried chilli. Yum!
Come only when the Japanese shop manager is in. If not the workers will just be busy talking among themselves.
Almost 3 years after my first tip left at this place, the quality has severely lacked which I believe, due to change of staff. This place used to be authentic and the ramen is strong in flavour.
Normal broth soup is excellent. Note that
Absolutely delicious  !! Had the Black spicy tonkotsu special.  Ramen had perfect texture, eggs were nice and gooey in the middle, broth was tasty.  Even better with ground sesame.
Teeny tiny place with really strong tasting ramen.
Order the cheapest ramen without any toppings is recommended! Free flow of hard boiled eggs, free bean sprouts. Note that the opening hours is DAILY: 11.30am–3pm, 6pm–10.30pm.
Authentic tastes, great broth and noodle texture.  Unfortunately the tonkotsu has gradually become less tender over the months - not sure why, but still my favorite ramen shop in Singapore.
Free flow eggs on your table!
best ramen ever
Black spicy ramen
Best ramen, new favorite replacing Marutama !
Discount coupon http://keisuke.sg/coupon.php but as of tip date it was for a free coke/sprite instead
One of the best ramen stalls in SG! Love the noodle texture and soup taste . Free flow of eggs and price is much cheaper than other ramen stalls of the same standard!
The chashu quality dropped. Was tough and flavorless. Soup was still ok
black spicy ramen is refreshingly delicious! very unique! reminds me of black pepper crab!
The free flow of sides (eggs & bean sprouts) do run out. Ask before you order.
Black spicy ramen!
Too salty.
Try black or red with everything added, strong flavour and more oil! Then walk to the end of the road for some lemon aiyu wintermelon tea. N maybe try the chicken. Miam!
Damn it's good! Best ramen ever!
Awesome tasty ramen
Authentic, delicious!
Every Thursday's!
I'd still go for the original. Just add special Egg and black fungus. Load on the free flow tau gey - crunchy simple yet delicious.
Flavoured egg does taste a level above the boiled. you will taste the difference in the yolk
Ramen is nice here. They have free flow hardboiled eggs.
Great Japanese Ramen! You can choose thickness of the soup, softness of noodles and chicken oil. + Free boiled egg! :)
Love the broth, especially mixing in the grounded sesame seeds. 😍
Love the boiled eggs (especially yummy) and the seasoned tau gay side dishes!
Love e unstingy spirit of this place. Free eggs, bean sprouts & uh tissue paper. E water's there even b4 u're seated. WIN.
Check the bill to avoid wrong billing. Ramen is good though. Free flow of hard boiled eggs and bean sprouts.
